The paper discusses strategies in games, which is a topic covered in the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category. The use of intelligence information suggests the involvement of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The logical system described in the paper falls under the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. The paper also discusses distributed knowledge, which is a topic covered in the Distributed Systems (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the interplay between coalition power modality and intelligence suggests the involvement of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
